According to Brig Leonard Hlathi, the SAPS and SARS at the border post did a routine check on a truck coming in from the Mozambican side. They found a hidden compartment and discovered drugs, alcohol and cash. Brig Leonard Hlathi and Memory Ndou of the SARS/SAPS Lebombo Border Post. A South African woman (48) and a Mozambican citizen were arrested. They will appear in the Komatipoort Magistrate’s Court tomorrow. Read all about this in this week’s Lowvelder. ALSO READ: Continued tobacco ban may cost South Africa billions, says TJSA founder